	<itunes:subtitle><![CDATA[
      
I guess this comes under the category of you should be careful what you absurdly joke about, lest it become true...
Ever since I
was a kid, if I saw a fly land in someone's soup, or on a friend
or family member's sandwich, I'd say &quot;hey, a little extra protein, no
charge&quot;...I seldom got much appreciation for the comment.But it seems I - and who knows how many others - may have been on to
something. Take a look that video clip below - wasp cookies are getting buzz in Japan!Apparently, wasp has been an ingredient in some kinds of
rice preparations in Japan for a long time, so making cookies with the winged creatures didn't seem like that big a leap.And - yes! - the wasp cookies are being touted for their protein content...But my tongue is probably barbed enough ... I expect I'll be sticking to sushi for my exotic protein...

       
    
    
    
      
        
          
        
